## Create project's environment

```http
POST /projects/org1/project1/environments HTTP/1.1
Host: <%= deploy_my_codes_api_url %>
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: <Your-API-Key>

{
  "name": "production",
  "strategy": "heroku"
}
```

```http
HTTP/1.1 201 CREATED
Content-Type: application/json
{
  "name": "production",
  "strategy": "heroku"
}
```

```shell
curl -XPOST <%= deploy_my_codes_api_url %>/projects/org1/project1/environments -H "Authorization:<Your-API-Key>" -d '{ "environment": { "name": "production", "strategy": "heroku" }}'

{
  "name": "production",
  "strategy": "heroku"
}
```

```ruby
require 'json'
require 'net/http'

url     = URI.parse('https://<%=  deploy_my_codes_api_url %>/projects/org1/project1/environments')
request = Net::HTTP::Post.new(url.to_s)
request['Authorization'] = '<Your-API-Key>'
request.body = { environment: { name: "production", strategy: "heroku" }}.to_json
result  = Net::HTTP.start(url.host, url.port) { |http| http.request(req) }
JSON.parse(result.body)
# {
#   "name": "production",
#   "strategy": "heroku"
# }
```
